                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/1186: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jordan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-12-29T22:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 29, 1921—10 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 30—9:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>93. Department’s 72, December 20, 6 p.m. and 73, December 29, 1 p.m. Haitian
                    Minister of [Finance] states through Minister of Foreign Affairs that Haitian
                    Government is prepared to pay note in question and will request from the bank
                    for the purpose, the statutory loan of $600,000 held by bank in accordance with
                    article 15 of bank concession and $500,000 in the hands of the bank in
                    conformity with article 8 of the transaction signed at Washington July 10,
                        1916.<note n="42" xml:id="d215fn42">
                        <ref target="frus1916#pg_358">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1916, p. 358</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jordan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
